sbml2modelica.preprocessing

Class SpeciesReferencePreprocessingManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.preprocessing.PreprocessingManager
      • sbml2modelica.preprocessing.SpeciesReferencePreprocessingManager

  • public class SpeciesReferencePreprocessingManager
extends PreprocessingManager
    A SpeciesReferencePreprocessingManager manipulates data in an SBML Model in order to make it easier the conversion of SBML SpeciesReferences into AbstractSpeciesReferences.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

    • Method Detail

      • getNextDefaultId

        private java.lang.String getNextDefaultId(boolean isReactant)
        This method returns the next serial default identifier for a SBML SpeciesReference. It continues to produce identifiers until it produces one that is not contained into the SBML Model.
        The method produces different identifiers for reactants and products.
        Parameters:
        isReactant - A boolean value that allows distinction between reactants and products when the identifier is generated.
        Returns:
        The next serial default identifier for a SBML SpeciesReference.

      • preprocessIdentifiers

        public void preprocessIdentifiers()
        This method sets the identifiers of all those SpeciesReferences with an undefined one to the serial default identifier.

      • preprocessInitialConditions

        public void preprocessInitialConditions(org.sbml.jsbml.SpeciesReference sr)
        This method pre-process a SBML SpeciesReference in order to setup its initial conditions.
        If the SpeciesReference is defined by an AssignmentRule, the method does nothing.
        If the SpeciesReference is not affected by any InitialAssignment, but its field stoichiometry is defined, an InitialAssignment with that value is created in the model.
        If the SpeciesReference does not appear in any AlgebraicRule and nothing else defines its initial value, then it is assumed to be zero.
        Parameters:
        sr - The SBML SpeciesReference to analyze.

      • preprocessDerivative

        public void preprocessDerivative(org.sbml.jsbml.SpeciesReference sr)
        This method pre-process a SBML SpeciesReference in order to setup the missing informations about its variability.
        If the SpeciesReference is constant, then the method does nothing.
        If there exists an AssignmentRule that defines the SpeciesReference, then the method does nothing.
        If there exists a RateRule that defines the SpeciesReference, then the method does nothing.
        If the SpeciesReference does not appears in any AlgebraicRule, then it is declared constant, if there is no Event that affect it, otherwise, a new RateRule with formula equals to zero is created to define the derivative of the SpeciesReference.
        Parameters:
        sr - The SBML SpeciesReference to analyze.

      • preprocessSpeciesReferences

        public void preprocessSpeciesReferences()
        This method applies the pre-proecssing procedures to every SpeciesReference in the Model.
